sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant YC as Your Code
    participant SDK as Anthropic SDK
    participant Server as Anthropic Servers
    participant LLM as LLM (model)

    rect rgb(42, 26, 74)
    Note over YC,LLM: NATIVE MODE — Anthropic does the parsing
    YC->>SDK: messages.create(<br/>  tools=[extract_schema],<br/>  messages=[...])
    SDK->>Server: HTTPS POST<br/>{tools, messages}
    Server->>LLM: prompt + tool schemas
    LLM-->>Server: raw text:<br/>"I'll call extract_transactions<br/>with raw_text=..."
    Note over Server: parses raw output<br/>validates against schema<br/>builds structured response
    Server-->>SDK: {content:[{<br/>  type:"tool_use",<br/>  name:"extract_transactions",<br/>  input:{raw_text:"..."}}],<br/>stop_reason:"tool_use"}
    SDK-->>YC: ToolUseBlock object<br/>(already typed)
    Note over YC: block.name = "extract_transactions"<br/>block.input = {raw_text:"..."}<br/>NO PARSING NEEDED
    YC->>YC: handler(**block.input)
    end

    rect rgb(15, 53, 40)
    Note over YC,LLM: REACT MODE — your code does the parsing
    YC->>SDK: messages.create(<br/>  messages=[...]<br/>  NO tools= PARAM)
    SDK->>Server: HTTPS POST<br/>{messages only}
    Server->>LLM: prompt (with JSON format<br/>instructions in system)
    LLM-->>Server: raw text:<br/>'{"action":"call_tool",<br/>"tool":"extract_transactions",<br/>"thought":"start parsing"}'
    Note over Server: NO parsing<br/>NO validation<br/>just text passthrough
    Server-->>SDK: {content:[{<br/>  type:"text",<br/>  text:"{\"action\":...}"}],<br/>stop_reason:"end_turn"}
    SDK-->>YC: TextBlock<br/>(just a string field)
    Note over YC: raw = block.text<br/>action = json.loads(raw)<br/>YOU PARSE IT
    YC->>YC: validate action shape
    YC->>YC: tool = action["tool"]<br/>handler = TOOL_HANDLERS[tool]<br/>handler(state, provider)
    end

    Note over YC,LLM: Both produce the same tool execution.<br/>Difference: where the JSON-from-text parsing happens.
